data.text:
Collection Information

Size: 15 Pages, Transcript

Format: Sound has been lost on tape reel; reel discarded.

Summary: An interview of William L. Warren conducted 1965 October 11, by Geoffrey Swift.

Biographical/Historical Note

William L. Warren was an art administrator in Connecticut. Worked on the Index of American Design.

Provenance

Conducted as part of the Archives of American Art's New Deal and the Arts project, which includes over 400 interviews of artists, administrators, historians, and others involved with the federal government's art programs and the activities of the Farm Security Administration in the 1930s and early 1940s.

Language Note

English .

Quotes and excerpts must be cited as follows: Oral history interview with William L. Warren, 1965 October 11. Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution.
